<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>Weblog - tomazursic.github.io - raspberry-pi</title><link href="/" rel="alternate"></link><link href="/feeds/raspberry-pi.tag.atom.xml" rel="self"></link><id>/</id><updated>2018-03-04T11:09:02+01:00</updated><entry><title>Exploring OBDII</title><link href="/exploring-obdii.html" rel="alternate"></link><published>2018-03-04T11:09:02+01:00</published><updated>2018-03-04T11:09:02+01:00</updated><author><name>Tomaz</name></author><id>tag:None,2018-03-04:/exploring-obdii.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;To satisfy the curiosity for reading car on-board diagnostics using&lt;/p&gt;</summary><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Raspberry PI with build in Bluetooth and ODBII Bluetooth adapter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Turn on the car engine after attaching the adapter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Setup:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example target device MAC address&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;00:19:5D:FE:9A:8F OBDII
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;Terminal 1:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Turn on the bluetoot and scan for adapter address&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ sudo bluetoothctl
    power on
    agent on
    default-agent
    scan on
    pair &lt;span class="m"&gt;00&lt;/span&gt;:19:5D:FE:9A:8F
    trust &lt;span class="m"&gt;00&lt;/span&gt;:19:5D:FE:9A:8F
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;Terminal 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;rfcomm associates the paired device ID with a serial device name&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo rfcomm &lt;span class="nb"&gt;bind&lt;/span&gt; rfcomm0 &lt;span class="m"&gt;00&lt;/span&gt;:19:5D:FE:9A:8F
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;Read output with pyobd&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;http://brendan-w.com/python-obd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nn"&gt;obd&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="n"&gt;connection&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;obd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;OBD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;/dev/rfcomm0&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="n"&gt;cmd&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;obd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;commands&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;RPM&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;connection&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;query&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;cmd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;value&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nb"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Example output:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="OBDII Output" src="/images/misc/obdII_output.jpg"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Unpairing a Bluetooth device&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start the Bluetooth utility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;bluetoothctl
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Unpair the Bluetooth device if required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;remove &amp;lt;dev&amp;gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Make sure the agent is stopped for the Bluetooth device.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;agent off
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Make sure the Bluetooth device is powered down.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;power off
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Exit the Bluetooth utility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;quit
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h2&gt;Release serail&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To remove the serial device do the following if required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;rfcomm release &lt;span class="m"&gt;00&lt;/span&gt;:19:5D:FE:9A:8F
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Shouldn't need this command, force rfdevices to stop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;rfkill list
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content><category term="notes"></category><category term="python"></category><category term="raspberry-pi"></category><category term="obd"></category></entry></feed>